sentences: Bildner studied Opera Performance at the Conservatorio Santa Cecilia in Rome, Italy, graduating in 1983.
After arriving in New York in 1990, Henry Threadgill heard Bildner sing and invited her to record with his ensemble Very Very Circus.

She appears on Too Much Sugar for a Dime (Axiom, 1993), Song Out of My Trees (Black Saint, 1993), and Carry the Day (Columbia, 1994) after which, with Threadgill's encouragement, she left the group to embark on her own projects.
